# Windsurf Rules for PromptShip
# These rules are automatically enforced on every AI code generation

## Critical Constraints

### File Structure
- NEVER create files outside src/{app,components,lib,hooks,stores,types,config}
- NEVER modify files in src/components/ui/ (shadcn primitives)
- ALWAYS use absolute imports with @/ alias
- NEVER use relative imports beyond parent directory

### Component Rules
- Server Components by default (no 'use client' unless interactive)
- Client Components ONLY for: useState, useEffect, event handlers, browser APIs
- ALWAYS group imports: react → next → third-party → local

### Database & Validation
- src/lib/db/schema.ts is the SINGLE SOURCE OF TRUTH
- ALWAYS validate user inputs with Zod before database operations
- NEVER use raw SQL queries (use Drizzle query builder)
- Types MUST derive from schema using $inferSelect and $inferInsert

### Styling
- ONLY Tailwind utility classes (no inline styles, no CSS modules)
- USE cn() from @/lib/utils/cn for conditional classes
- NEVER use style={{ }} prop

### Authentication & Security
- ALWAYS check auth in API routes and Server Actions
- NEVER trust client-side auth state for authorization
- ALWAYS use environment variables for secrets
- ALWAYS implement rate limiting on public endpoints

### API Routes Pattern
1. Rate limiting first
2. Authentication check
3. Zod validation
4. Business logic
5. Structured response

### TypeScript
- NEVER use 'any' type
- ALWAYS define proper interfaces/types
- USE type inference from Drizzle schema

### State Management
- Server state → React Query (@tanstack/react-query)
- Client state → Zustand (src/stores/)
- Form state → React Hook Form + Zod

### Naming Conventions
- Components: PascalCase (LoginForm.tsx)
- Utilities: kebab-case (rate-limit.ts)
- Functions: camelCase (getUserById)
- Constants: UPPER_SNAKE_CASE (MAX_PROMPTS)

### Error Handling
- ALWAYS wrap risky operations in try-catch
- ALWAYS return structured errors: { success: boolean, error?: string, data?: T }
- NEVER expose internal errors to client

### Performance
- USE Server Components for static content
- USE dynamic imports for heavy components
- USE loading.tsx and error.tsx in routes
- AVOID client-side data fetching when server-side possible

## Before Every Generation

1. ✅ Check AGENTS.md for detailed patterns
2. ✅ Verify file location matches structure
3. ✅ Check if similar code exists
4. ✅ Use existing utilities (don't recreate)
5. ✅ Add Zod validation for inputs
6. ✅ Add error handling
7. ✅ Use TypeScript strictly
8. ✅ Match existing code style

## Red Flags (STOP if you see these)

- Creating folders outside defined structure
- Using 'any' type
- Skipping validation
- Hardcoding API keys or secrets
- Inline styles or CSS modules
- Modifying src/components/ui/
- Client Component for static content
- Missing error handling
- Relative imports like '../../../'

## AI Provider Integration

- NEVER instantiate Anthropic/OpenAI directly in components
- ALWAYS use abstracted clients from @/lib/ai/
- ALWAYS return structured GeneratedCode interface

## Payment Integration

- Support BOTH Stripe and Razorpay
- Webhook handlers in app/api/webhooks/[provider]/
- ALWAYS implement idempotency
- ALWAYS create audit trail

